name: Purple Paralysis
description: Purple Paralysis, bred by Cream of the Crop, is a sativa-dominant hybrid with potently energizing effects and a hashy lavender aroma. Its genetics are a cross between Power Plant and Lavender, and this strain also goes by the name "Jellyfish Bud."
descriptionPlain: Purple Paralysis, bred by Cream of the Crop, is a sativa-dominant hybrid with potently energizing effects and a hashy lavender aroma. Its genetics are a cross between Power Plant and Lavender, and this strain also goes by the name "Jellyfish Bud."

highlightedReviews.text: obviously i loved this strain, but no strain can be flawless. this strain will make you feel very relaxed, and comfortable regardless of the circumstanses, but in a way, it makes you too lazy. i tried to take my phone out to take a picture, but i couldnt even summon enough energy to press the button. other than the unbeleivable laziness, this weed is amazing

Structurally it's very sativa like with long, thinner but still dense buds. It's flavor is very sweet and unlike any other strain I've tried. Honey like is the closest flavor I could put it at. Effects wise it doesn't hit the same notes as other sativa dominant hybrids but rather behaves like an indica without the extra coma like symptoms. It's a very relaxed, not anxiety inducing kind of feeling. Most suitable for a nice evening toke post dinner (or pre if you like to eat after) because I became very hungry after.

articles.title: New Strains Alert: Frankenstein, Lavender Jones, Purple Paralysis, Space Jill, and Sugar Kush
articles.author: Kayla Williams
articles.text:
Based on submissions made by Leafly users, we've added Frankenstein, Lavender Jones, Purple Paralysis, Space Jill, and Sugar Kush to the Leafly Explorer. Keep 'em coming! Also, we've got plently more new strains on the way, so stay tuned. In the meantime, leave a strain review if you've had the chance to try any of these new varieties, and let us know which strains you'd love for us to add next so we can make sure we don't forget any of your favorites!
1. Frankenstein
Characteristics of Frankenstein:

80% indica
Unknown lineage
Recommended for consumers with a high cannabis tolerance or patients with severe symptoms
Genetics gave rise to Opal OG Kush, Copper Kush, Sweet Lafayette, and OG's Pearl

2. Lavender Jones
Characteristics of Lavender Jones:

Hybrid strain
Cross between Casey Jones and Purple Urkle
Buds express themselves in vibrant hues of purple and green
Can bring deep relaxation paired with dreamy cerebral euphoria
Indoor flowering time of 7 to 8 weeks

3. Purple Paralysis
Characteristics of Purple Paralysis:

Sativa-dominant hybrid
Also known as Jellyfish Bud
Cross between Power Plant and Lavender
Breeder: Cream of the Crop
Hashy lavender aroma
Has potently energizing effects
Indoor flowering time of about 67 days

4. Space Jill
Characteristics of Space Jill:

70% sativa strain
Cross between Romulan and Cinderella 99
Recreation of the Space Queen strain
Breeder: TGA Genetics
Sweet mango and candy aroma
Can bring high-energy, creative, productive effects

5. Sugar Kush
Characteristics of Sugar Kush:

Indica-dominant strain
Cross between Kandy Kush and Hash Plant
Indoor flowering time of 9 weeks

growInfo.growNotes: Suitable for SCROG and SOG setups
